questionContent.body:
Scenario: University Course Enrollment System

ER Diagram Description:

Entities and Attributes:



  • Student (StudentID, Name, Email)
  • Course (CourseID, Title, Credits)
  • Enrollment (EnrollmentID, Grade)
  • Faculty (FacultyID, Name, Department)
  • Teaches (Links Faculty and Course)
  • Enrollment connects Student and Course

Scenario: Hospital Management System

  • Entities and Relationships:
  • Patient(PatientID, Name, Age, Gender, Address)
  • Doctor(DoctorID, Name, Specialization)
  • Appointment(AppointmentID, Date, Time, PatientID, DoctorID)
  • Prescription(PrescriptionID, AppointmentID, Medicine, Dosage)
  • Diagnosis(DiagnosisID, AppointmentID, Symptoms, Disease)
  • A patient can have many appointments with doctors.
  • Each appointment may lead to one or more prescriptions and diagnoses.

Scenario: College Examination System

Context:

A college maintains a database to manage exam results.

  • Each Student has a Roll Number, Name, and Email.
  • Each Course has a unique Course ID, Course Name, and Credits.
  • Each Exam is linked to a course and has an Exam ID, Date, and Type (Midterm/Final).
  • A Student can appear in many exams and receives a Score for each attempt.
  • A Faculty teaches a course and prepares the exam. Faculty has ID, Name, and Department.

Scenario:

A university stores data about students, departments, and the courses they register for.

  • Each student has a name, roll number, and multiple phone numbers.
  • Each student belongs to one department.
  • A department can offer many courses.
  • A student can enroll in multiple courses (many-to-many).
